reviewText: First of all, it is a movie that has been transferred onto dvd with poor quality and very un professional. This movie tells the story of Snow White with a tiny bit of skin, but No sex!  The acting is poor and not worthy of viewing.  If you want to line the pockets of whoever the money goes to, it's your business but be ware you were Warned!!!

Well, first off, I understand why they put an X rating on the cover so it wouldn't be mistaken for a children's classic.  For today's rating system, it would be PG-13 at best.  It is a fun frolic with Marie (Snow White) frolicking around the forest, running from the a myriad of forest creatures that had once been princes & the evil queen.  Cinderella & her sister's make a scene or 2 as well as Sleeping Beauty & her family.  Technically speaking, it was a poor print.  Overall tho, it was a fun movie but not a great one.  If you are a fan of Marie, then it's a must have.
Not exactly what I expected. Did not quite live up to the review I read elsewhere. Fast fulfillment as usual.

Howdy;

The title is a bit misleading for it is not just "Snow White" but several other fairy tales as well.

It is a fun romp from one tail to another, but a bit hard to follow at times.  The video quality is sadly on the bad side, but viewable.  It was fun to watch and a good addition to my collection.

If you are looking for a real off-the-wall movie, this just might be it.
